WEBVTT

1
00:00:59.840 --> 00:01:01.956
Sorry. man. I know this hurts.

2
00:01:05.840 --> 00:01:09.549
Michael told me you pulled
the bullet outwith your bare hands.

3
00:01:09.640 --> 00:01:12.598
You'll have to show me
how to do that sometime.

4
00:01:13.560 --> 00:01:15.551
Where is she?

5
00:01:17.200 --> 00:01:19.236
- What? I didn't...
- Where is she?

6
00:01:20.600 --> 00:01:25.037
You mean Kate? She's been watching
over you for the past 24 hours straight.

7
00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:28.556
Only way I could get rid of her
was to send her to get food for you.

8
00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:37.751
I love her.

9
00:03:02.480 --> 00:03:05.278
Hey. girl. What are you doing here?

10
00:03:09.920 --> 00:03:12.912
- Hey. there.
- All right. Let's get you to bed.

11
00:03:21.480 --> 00:03:23.596
Watch your step.
Watch your step.

12
00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:28.070
What the hell is that smell?

13
00:03:28.160 --> 00:03:30.515
- Probably your breath.
- Yeah. right.

14
00:03:30.600 --> 00:03:32.795
- Come on.
- Wow.

15
00:03:40.880 --> 00:03:42.871
You're beautiful.

16
00:03:44.960 --> 00:03:46.598
Hey.

17
00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:50.599
Hey. I just gave you a compliment.

18
00:03:51.280 --> 00:03:53.271
Yeah. I heard you.

19
00:03:57.240 --> 00:03:59.879
Aren't you gonna
take my pants off first?

20
00:04:08.080 --> 00:04:10.150
You are beautiful.

21
00:04:16.360 --> 00:04:18.237
Good night.

22
00:05:27.400 --> 00:05:29.516
Coffee? Pie? Both?

23
00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:32.319
- How about a beer?
- I'd like to see some ID.

24
00:05:33.320 --> 00:05:34.878
I'm 24. Ma.

25
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:38.032
You wanna ride on that death trap
of yours without a helmet.

26
00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:41.032
I'm not gonna help your cause
by getting you drunk.

27
00:05:47.320 --> 00:05:50.551
- How's that wrist?
- What? This?

28
00:05:52.440 --> 00:05:55.432
You know that shelf in the kitchen
sticks out sometimes.

29
00:05:55.520 --> 00:05:58.080
- You'd think I'd remember it was there.
- Don't.

30
00:06:06.040 --> 00:06:08.270
I made my bed. Katherine.

31
00:06:09.160 --> 00:06:11.116
Well. your bed's gone. Ma.

32
00:06:11.760 --> 00:06:13.432
What?

33
00:06:20.760 --> 00:06:22.557
What is this?

34
00:06:22.640 --> 00:06:25.200
- An insurance policy for the house.
- I never...

35
00:06:25.280 --> 00:06:27.714
I took it out in your name.

36
00:06:33.200 --> 00:06:35.316
What did you do?

37
00:06:35.400 --> 00:06:37.675
Does Wayne know about this?

38
00:06:41.600 --> 00:06:44.194
Just remember you were here
and you didn't see me.

39
00:06:44.280 --> 00:06:46.714
Katherine! What did you do?

40
00:06:47.480 --> 00:06:49.471
I took care of you. Ma.

41
00:06:51.040 --> 00:06:54.237
I gotta go.
You're not gonna see me for a while.

42
00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:08.558
Katherine. What did you do?

43
00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:11.717
Katherine!

44
00:07:16.840 --> 00:07:18.831
- Hey-
- Hey-

45
00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:23.152
You OK?

46
00:07:23.240 --> 00:07:27.358
Yeah. yeah. I think I'm just...
I think I'm tired.

47
00:07:31.080 --> 00:07:33.435
- How is he?
- Fever's still up there.

48
00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:37.073
Can't tell if the antibiotics
are working.

49
00:07:37.160 --> 00:07:39.071
It'll help to get some food in him.

50
00:07:39.160 --> 00:07:42.835
You should get down to the beach
for Shannon.

51
00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:48.236
I was actually thinking
that I should stay and watch Sawyer.

52
00:07:49.040 --> 00:07:51.031
I'll stay with him.

53
00:07:51.120 --> 00:07:53.554
You should be there.

54
00:07:59.040 --> 00:08:02.953
Keep him hydrated. Maybe mash up some
fruit and see if you can get him to eat.

55
00:08:03.040 --> 00:08:06.669
Everybody will be at the beach.
so don't forget the button.

56
00:08:06.760 --> 00:08:08.159
I've got it.

57
00:08:08.240 --> 00:08:10.913
- I'll be back in a couple hours.
- Yep.

58
00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:15.996
You're sure you're OK?

59
00:08:17.640 --> 00:08:19.631
Yeah. I'm great.

60
00:08:33.560 --> 00:08:34.959
Hey.

61
00:08:38.320 --> 00:08:40.675
I'm going to go to the funeral.

62
00:08:45.320 --> 00:08:47.436
I don't think I'm gonna make it.

63
00:08:57.360 --> 00:09:00.397
I think most of them realise
it was an accident. Ana.

64
00:09:41.840 --> 00:09:43.990
Shannon and I were strangers.

65
00:09:45.800 --> 00:09:48.030
We never would have met if...

66
00:09:52.920 --> 00:09:55.229
We wouldn't even have spoken if...

67
00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:02.991
But we did meet.

68
00:10:04.040 --> 00:10:06.156
And we did speak.

69
00:10:10.240 --> 00:10:12.231
At least.

70
00:10:22.120 --> 00:10:24.236
I loved her.

71
00:11:01.080 --> 00:11:03.310
May she rest in peace.

72
00:11:27.600 --> 00:11:29.397
You hungry?

73
00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:32.074
I'm just gonna mash you up
some fruit here.

74
00:11:34.200 --> 00:11:38.193
When you wake up. you're gonna get a
kick out of me feeding you like a baby.

75
00:11:42.840 --> 00:11:44.956
I saw a horse.

76
00:11:48.160 --> 00:11:49.559
Yeah.

77
00:11:49.640 --> 00:11:52.359
That's what happens
when you don't sleep.

78
00:12:02.160 --> 00:12:04.594
Sawyer? You awake?

79
00:12:10.200 --> 00:12:11.633
You killed me.

80
00:12:12.840 --> 00:12:15.149
Why did you kill me?

81
00:12:22.840 --> 00:12:24.671
It's the alarm.

82
00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:28.558
Kate!

83
00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:29.709
Kate!

84
00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:39.232
Sawyer!

85
00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:43.990
4. 8....

86
00:12:44.080 --> 00:12:46.196
15. 16. 2...

87
00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:53.319
42.

88
00:13:02.520 --> 00:13:05.193
- What happened?
- I don't know.

89
00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:07.396
- Well. you said...
- I don't know. John!

90
00:13:08.360 --> 00:13:10.032
Well. where's Kate?

91
00:13:13.040 --> 00:13:15.031
Kate. Hey.

92
00:13:16.240 --> 00:13:19.630
- You missed the funeral.
- Yeah. I was with Sawyer.

93
00:13:20.720 --> 00:13:22.358
Oh. right.

94
00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:25.159
A few of "them" came. The new people.

95
00:13:26.560 --> 00:13:30.235
Not her. the one who killed Shannon.
That would've been a bit awkward.

96
00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:32.629
They seem to have had
a rough time of it.

97
00:13:32.840 --> 00:13:35.957
Looks like they went bloody
Lord of the Flies out there.

98
00:13:39.200 --> 00:13:41.589
You haven't listened to a word
I've said.

99
00:13:42.920 --> 00:13:45.992
- Do you think there are horses here?
- What?

100
00:13:46.800 --> 00:13:48.711
I think I saw a horse in the jungle.

101
00:13:50.440 --> 00:13:52.590
I've seen polar bears.

102
00:13:52.680 --> 00:13:55.558
I've seen monsters.
Well. heard monsters.

103
00:13:55.640 --> 00:13:58.518
But horses? No.

104
00:13:59.240 --> 00:14:01.834
Kate. where are you going?

105
00:14:09.080 --> 00:14:11.196
Tallahassee. one way. please.

106
00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:15.072
Tallahassee? I spent a week
in Tallahassee one night.

107
00:14:15.880 --> 00:14:18.917
It's all strip malls and waffle houses.

108
00:14:19.000 --> 00:14:22.117
What's a pretty girl like you
gonna do down in Tallahassee?

109
00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:25.795
- I'm sure I'll find something.
- Bet you've got family down there.

110
00:14:25.880 --> 00:14:27.916
Actually. I'm just visiting.

111
00:14:30.480 --> 00:14:31.674
Hey.

112
00:14:32.520 --> 00:14:34.317
Hey.

113
00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:37.476
Don't I know you?

114
00:14:45.160 --> 00:14:47.196
No. I don't think so.

115
00:14:48.080 --> 00:14:49.957
Don't run. Kate.

116
00:14:56.400 --> 00:14:58.118
I got her.

117
00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:00.634
Kate Austen.
you're under arrest for murder.

118
00:15:00.720 --> 00:15:02.790
- I didn't do anything.
- Yeah. you did.

119
00:15:02.880 --> 00:15:05.075
Your mama gave you up. Kate.

120
00:15:18.560 --> 00:15:20.869
Charlie. Have you seen Kate?

121
00:15:21.480 --> 00:15:23.471
A little while ago in the jungle.

122
00:15:23.560 --> 00:15:26.518
She was acting kind of barmy.
asking me about horses.

123
00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:28.750
You know where she is now?

124
00:15:28.840 --> 00:15:31.513
She's on the path
heading back to the caves.

125
00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:36.877
- Everything OK?
- Yeah. Charlie. Everything's fine.

126
00:15:49.240 --> 00:15:52.391
- Thank you.
- Free at last. huh?

127
00:16:01.440 --> 00:16:03.908
Yeah. man. Looks good.

128
00:16:12.440 --> 00:16:15.591
Hey. Locke.
what's up with the blast doors?

129
00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:18.558
Blast doors?

130
00:16:20.080 --> 00:16:25.473
Yeah. Like. in case of an explosion.
they come from the ceiling.

131
00:16:25.560 --> 00:16:28.120
- That guy down here...
- Desmond?

132
00:16:28.200 --> 00:16:32.352
- He didn't tell you what they were for?
- No. No. he didn't.

133
00:16:34.840 --> 00:16:37.149
But he did leave a movie.

134
00:16:37.240 --> 00:16:39.629
- A movie?
- Yeah.

135
00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:43.034
You wanna see it?

136
00:16:43.120 --> 00:16:44.917
I would like to see it. too.

137
00:16:48.480 --> 00:16:50.471
If you don't mind.

138
00:16:53.640 --> 00:16:56.154
Why not? The more. the merrier.

139
00:17:10.960 --> 00:17:13.997
Kate.
what the hell are you doing out here?

140
00:17:16.880 --> 00:17:19.678
What happened in the hatch. Kate?
Why did you leave?

141
00:17:19.760 --> 00:17:22.433
I find Sawyer on the ground.
You just took off...

142
00:17:22.520 --> 00:17:25.353
- Is he OK?
- Yes. Kate. he's fine.

143
00:17:29.120 --> 00:17:31.953
- I'm sorry.
- Are you?

144
00:17:35.920 --> 00:17:37.797
Yeah. I'm sorry.

145
00:17:37.880 --> 00:17:40.872
I'm sorry that I am not
as perfect as you.

146
00:17:40.960 --> 00:17:43.190
I'm sorry that I'm not as good!

147
00:17:44.880 --> 00:17:47.314
- What's going on with you?
- Just forget it.

148
00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:49.436
- Don't walk away from me.
- Let go of me.

149
00:17:49.520 --> 00:17:51.238
- No. Kate.
- Don't!

150
00:17:51.800 --> 00:17:53.870
It's OK. It's OK.

151
00:17:54.760 --> 00:17:55.954
Hey.

152
00:17:56.040 --> 00:17:59.077
Jack. This place is crazy. It's just...

153
00:18:00.160 --> 00:18:02.913
I can't... It's driving me nuts.

154
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:04.991
I know. It's OK.

155
00:18:05.080 --> 00:18:08.072
It's all right. It's all right.

156
00:18:08.840 --> 00:18:10.592
All right?

157
00:18:52.480 --> 00:18:53.833
Kate!

158
00:18:58.240 --> 00:19:00.470
From the moment the alarm sounds.

159
00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:05.554
you will have four minutes to enter the
code into the microcomputer processor...

160
00:19:05.640 --> 00:19:07.517
“induction into the program.

161
00:19:07.600 --> 00:19:12.355
When the alarm sounds. either you
or your partner must input the code.

162
00:19:13.160 --> 00:19:17.233
It is highly recommended that you and
your partner take alternating shifts.

163
00:19:17.320 --> 00:19:20.198
In this manner.
you will both stay as fresh and alert...

164
00:19:20.280 --> 00:19:23.113
...utmost importance
that when the alarm sounds.

165
00:19:23.200 --> 00:19:26.795
the code be entered correctly
and in a timely fashion.

166
00:19:26.880 --> 00:19:30.350
Do not attempt to use
the computer for anything...

167
00:19:31.080 --> 00:19:32.752
Congratulations.

168
00:19:32.840 --> 00:19:37.470
Until your replacements arrive. the
future of the project is in your hands.

169
00:19:37.560 --> 00:19:40.552
On behalf of the DeGroots. Alvar Hanso.

170
00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:43.108
and all of us at the Dharma Initiative.

171
00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:48.194
thank you. namaste.
and good luck.

172
00:19:52.080 --> 00:19:53.672
All right.

173
00:19:53.760 --> 00:19:58.356
So. you've been pushing that button
every two hours since you got down here?

174
00:19:58.440 --> 00:20:00.032
That's right.

175
00:20:00.840 --> 00:20:02.637
How's that even work?

176
00:20:02.720 --> 00:20:06.679
I've set up two-person shifts.
Six hours. Everyone's on the roster.

177
00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:09.797
Don't they wanna know why?

178
00:20:09.880 --> 00:20:12.269
I think the film's
pretty self-explanatory.

179
00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:17.115
Really? All I heard was something
about electromagnets and an "incident".

180
00:20:17.200 --> 00:20:19.350
What about all the missing pieces?

181
00:20:19.440 --> 00:20:21.158
You mean the splices?

182
00:20:21.240 --> 00:20:24.198
Just a frame here and there. I think.
Nothing important.

183
00:20:24.280 --> 00:20:26.271
What do you think?

184
00:20:28.480 --> 00:20:30.436
About the film? What do you think?

185
00:21:13.080 --> 00:21:15.469
I'm sorry I missed it. Her funeral.

186
00:21:15.560 --> 00:21:17.869
I had to be with Sawyer. so...

187
00:21:19.520 --> 00:21:22.193
Why aren't you with him now?

188
00:21:26.520 --> 00:21:28.590
Because I'm going crazy.

189
00:21:37.120 --> 00:21:39.190
Do you believe in ghosts. Sayid?

190
00:21:42.120 --> 00:21:45.954
I saw Walt in the jungle.
just before Shannon was shot.

191
00:21:56.600 --> 00:21:58.989
Does that make me crazy?

192
00:22:15.680 --> 00:22:19.070
It's a long drive back
to the arraignment. You comfy?

193
00:22:32.240 --> 00:22:34.231
Why now?

194
00:22:36.640 --> 00:22:39.996
- What?
- Nice. corn-fed farm girl like you.

195
00:22:40.080 --> 00:22:45.359
No history of violence. Straight A's.
No record. couple of speeding tickets.

196
00:22:46.480 --> 00:22:48.948
I just gotta wonder.
why did you kill him now?

197
00:22:51.880 --> 00:22:55.589
Right. yeah. don't tell me. You wouldn't
wanna incriminate yourself.

198
00:22:55.680 --> 00:22:58.069
Not after you were so smart planning it.

199
00:22:58.760 --> 00:23:02.878
That jury back in Iowa sure ain't
gonna get hung up on premeditation.

200
00:23:02.960 --> 00:23:04.996
And a gas leak?

201
00:23:05.080 --> 00:23:09.039
Come on. That's amateur hour
from top to bottom.

202
00:23:09.120 --> 00:23:11.395
Sounds like
you've got it all figured out.

203
00:23:11.480 --> 00:23:14.916
- I have you all figured out.
- You don't know anything about me.

204
00:23:15.000 --> 00:23:18.879
White-trash mom divorces dad. starts up
with some guy who's a drinker.

205
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:22.236
Maybe he knocks her around a little bit.
so she marries him.

206
00:23:22.320 --> 00:23:24.880
because. you know. that's what happens.

207
00:23:25.720 --> 00:23:28.792
Then this drunk. this Wayne.
he moves into your house.

208
00:23:28.880 --> 00:23:32.350
And you get to lay there every night
and listen to him doing your mom

209
00:23:32.440 --> 00:23:34.749
right there in your daddy's old bedroom.

210
00:23:34.840 --> 00:23:38.355
And even that wouldn't be so bad
if he didn't beat her up all the time.

211
00:23:38.440 --> 00:23:41.318
But she loves him.

212
00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:43.152
She defends him.

213
00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:52.279
If that don't make a person want to kill
somebody. I don't know what does.

214
00:23:52.360 --> 00:23:54.874
But the question is: now. why now?

215
00:23:56.040 --> 00:24:00.511
Why after all these years did you
just decide to blow poor Wayne up?

216
00:24:06.200 --> 00:24:08.714
He come knocking on your door
late at night?

217
00:24:10.360 --> 00:24:12.555
He never touched me.

218
00:24:16.560 --> 00:24:18.073
Look out!

219
00:25:18.240 --> 00:25:20.515
Why can't you
just put the numbers in now?

220
00:25:20.600 --> 00:25:23.910
No. Doesn't work that way.
The alarm goes off at four minutes.

221
00:25:24.000 --> 00:25:25.991
You can't type anything until then.

222
00:25:31.800 --> 00:25:34.189
You mind if I check out
some of this hardware?

223
00:25:35.480 --> 00:25:36.959
Sure.

224
00:25:38.720 --> 00:25:40.711
Just don't break it.

225
00:25:51.480 --> 00:25:53.994
- Hello. again.
- Hello.

226
00:25:57.080 --> 00:25:59.469
I have something I think you should see.

227
00:26:05.840 --> 00:26:08.957
If you don't mind.
I will begin at the beginning.

228
00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:18.959
Long before Christ. the King of Judah
was a man named Josiah.

229
00:26:19.800 --> 00:26:22.837
Boy. when you say "beginning".
you mean "beginning".

230
00:26:24.960 --> 00:26:29.909
At that time. the temple where
the people worshipped was in ruin.

231
00:26:31.040 --> 00:26:33.474
And so the people worshipped idols.

232
00:26:33.960 --> 00:26:37.839
False gods.
And so. the kingdom was in disarray.

233
00:26:38.920 --> 00:26:42.708
Josiah. since he was a good king.

234
00:26:42.800 --> 00:26:49.035
sent his secretary to the treasury
and said "We must rebuild the temple".

235
00:26:50.160 --> 00:26:53.596
"Give all of the gold to the workers
so that this will be done."

236
00:26:54.720 --> 00:26:59.350
But when the secretary returned.
he had no gold.

237
00:27:01.280 --> 00:27:03.555
And when Josiah asked why this was.

238
00:27:04.920 --> 00:27:07.150
the secretary replied...

239
00:27:12.320 --> 00:27:14.038
"We found a book".

240
00:27:17.080 --> 00:27:20.755
- Do you know this story?
- No. Afraid I don't.

241
00:27:22.160 --> 00:27:26.915
What the secretary had found
was an ancient book.

242
00:27:28.800 --> 00:27:30.950
The Book of Law.

243
00:27:32.640 --> 00:27:35.029
You may know it as the Old Testament.

244
00:27:36.840 --> 00:27:39.832
And it was with that ancient book.

245
00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:42.831
not with the gold.

246
00:27:42.920 --> 00:27:45.229
that Josiah rebuilt the temple.

247
00:27:49.520 --> 00:27:51.750
On the other side of the island...

248
00:27:54.480 --> 00:27:56.869
we found a place much like this.

249
00:27:59.840 --> 00:28:03.549
And in this place we found a book.

250
00:28:16.280 --> 00:28:20.398
I believe what's inside there
will be of great value to you.

251
00:29:11.160 --> 00:29:12.559
Hey.

252
00:29:19.360 --> 00:29:21.954
So. Rose's husband's white.

253
00:29:23.600 --> 00:29:27.434
- Didn't see that one coming.
- Is there something you need. Hurley?

254
00:29:27.520 --> 00:29:30.353
Nope. Just taking a walk.

255
00:29:30.440 --> 00:29:31.953
Thought I'd say hey.

256
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:37.110
Who's taking care of Sawyer?

257
00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:38.519
Sun is.

258
00:29:38.600 --> 00:29:40.830
So you're. like. mad at him?

259
00:29:44.400 --> 00:29:46.197
Why would I be mad at Sawyer?

260
00:29:46.280 --> 00:29:49.113
Maybe because he's the one
who always comes down here

261
00:29:49.200 --> 00:29:51.316
and chops wood and now you are.

262
00:29:52.400 --> 00:29:54.595
It's. like. transference.

263
00:29:55.760 --> 00:29:56.954
Are you a shrink now?

264
00:29:57.040 --> 00:29:59.918
That's what they called it
in the mental hospital.

265
00:30:01.160 --> 00:30:03.151
I'm not mad at anyone.

266
00:30:14.560 --> 00:30:16.630
Where's Jack?

267
00:30:16.720 --> 00:30:18.995
I don't know. He didn't come back.

268
00:30:21.200 --> 00:30:23.236
Has he said anything?

269
00:30:24.360 --> 00:30:25.759
Sawyer?

270
00:30:26.960 --> 00:30:29.394
No. He's still sleeping.

271
00:30:32.680 --> 00:30:34.875
Can you watch him?

272
00:30:36.440 --> 00:30:39.716
- I can stay if you...
- No. yeah. I can.

273
00:30:39.800 --> 00:30:41.279
Thanks.

274
00:31:02.080 --> 00:31:03.308
Right.

275
00:31:04.960 --> 00:31:07.599
Yes.
I'm sure that's the exact form you got.

276
00:31:10.560 --> 00:31:13.028
I'll send one over to you. right.

277
00:31:16.240 --> 00:31:18.037
I'll call you back later.

278
00:31:25.280 --> 00:31:26.918
Hi. Dad.

279
00:31:30.440 --> 00:31:33.193
The police and the US Marshals
are looking for you.

280
00:31:33.280 --> 00:31:36.192
- You shouldn't have come.
- I was outside for two hours.

281
00:31:36.280 --> 00:31:38.350
They're not here.

282
00:31:39.160 --> 00:31:41.230
Is it true? What they're saying?

283
00:31:46.960 --> 00:31:48.837
Katie. what did you come here for?

284
00:31:52.160 --> 00:31:54.151
Why didn't you tell me. Dad?

285
00:31:55.240 --> 00:31:56.878
Tell you what?

286
00:31:58.720 --> 00:32:02.235
I was making a scrapbook.
A surprise for your birthday.

287
00:32:04.200 --> 00:32:07.510
So I called one of your COs
to get some pictures of you in uniform.

288
00:32:08.520 --> 00:32:11.034
The pictures he sent me
had dates on the back.

289
00:32:11.120 --> 00:32:14.874
Photos of you in Korea. up until
four months before I was born.

290
00:32:21.280 --> 00:32:24.033
Why didn't you tell me
that Wayne was my father?

291
00:32:27.760 --> 00:32:29.478
Why?

292
00:32:37.680 --> 00:32:40.148
I didn't tell you
because I knew you'd kill him.

293
00:32:45.080 --> 00:32:48.959
And your mother loved him.

294
00:32:54.640 --> 00:32:57.791
You were five years old.
I wanted to take you along with me

295
00:32:57.880 --> 00:32:59.871
but she wouldn't let me.

296
00:33:01.960 --> 00:33:03.837
So why didn't you kill him?

297
00:33:10.960 --> 00:33:13.394
Because I don't have murder in my heart.

298
00:33:24.720 --> 00:33:27.109
I'm gonna have to call them.

299
00:33:32.960 --> 00:33:35.076
Can I have an hour?

300
00:33:55.440 --> 00:33:57.078
Bye. Daddy.

301
00:34:27.600 --> 00:34:29.591
Can you hear me?

302
00:34:32.800 --> 00:34:34.313
Sawyer?

303
00:34:50.000 --> 00:34:51.911
Wayne?

304
00:34:59.760 --> 00:35:01.830
I'm probably crazy...

305
00:35:03.600 --> 00:35:05.670
and this doesn't matter...

306
00:35:08.440 --> 00:35:11.557
but maybe you're in there. somehow.

307
00:35:12.440 --> 00:35:14.510
And you asked me a question.

308
00:35:15.240 --> 00:35:17.231
You asked me why I...

309
00:35:19.240 --> 00:35:21.231
Why I did it.

310
00:35:25.200 --> 00:35:27.634
It wasn't because
you drove my father away.

311
00:35:28.600 --> 00:35:30.830
Or the way you looked at me.

312
00:35:33.640 --> 00:35:35.835
Or because you beat her.

313
00:35:39.760 --> 00:35:42.638
It was because I hated
that you were part of me.

314
00:35:42.720 --> 00:35:45.712
That I would never be good.

315
00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:47.995
That I would never have anything good.

316
00:35:48.880 --> 00:35:51.075
And every time that I look at Sawyer.

317
00:35:51.160 --> 00:35:53.355
every time I feel something for him.

318
00:35:55.120 --> 00:35:57.111
I see you. Wayne.

319
00:35:57.920 --> 00:35:59.990
And it makes me sick.

320
00:36:05.080 --> 00:36:07.913
That's about the sweetest thing
I ever heard.

321
00:36:09.560 --> 00:36:11.232
Sawyer?

322
00:36:12.680 --> 00:36:14.875
Who the hell is Wayne?

323
00:36:25.080 --> 00:36:28.117
Am I in a bunk bed?

324
00:36:32.200 --> 00:36:34.350
Yeah. you're in a bunk bed.

325
00:36:35.920 --> 00:36:37.911
Are we saved?

326
00:36:42.480 --> 00:36:44.596
No. Sawyer.

327
00:36:44.680 --> 00:36:46.318
Not yet.

328
00:37:00.840 --> 00:37:02.159
Voilà.

329
00:37:03.640 --> 00:37:06.108
What are the odds?

330
00:37:06.200 --> 00:37:08.156
- The odds?
- Yeah.

331
00:37:08.800 --> 00:37:13.032
Here. hold this down on the table there.
nice and flat.

332
00:37:16.520 --> 00:37:20.798
I mean. think about it.
Somebody made this film.

333
00:37:22.840 --> 00:37:27.152
Someone else cut this piece out.

334
00:37:29.200 --> 00:37:33.557
We crash. two halves of the same plane
fall on different parts of the island.

335
00:37:33.640 --> 00:37:35.915
You're over there. I'm over here.

336
00:37:37.320 --> 00:37:40.915
And now here's the missing piece.
right back where it belongs.

337
00:37:43.200 --> 00:37:45.236
What are the odds?

338
00:37:46.880 --> 00:37:49.872
Don't mistake coincidence for fate.

339
00:38:04.880 --> 00:38:07.189
You've gotta be kidding me.

340
00:38:07.280 --> 00:38:09.475
Airlock's over this way.

341
00:38:11.080 --> 00:38:14.231
Come on. admit it. We've been rescued.

342
00:38:18.440 --> 00:38:20.431
You got it? Sorry.

343
00:38:21.240 --> 00:38:23.231
Watch yourself.

344
00:38:31.800 --> 00:38:33.791
Son of a bitch.

345
00:38:36.320 --> 00:38:38.197
Watch yourself. OK?

346
00:38:41.160 --> 00:38:42.957
- I got it.
- OK.

347
00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:49.396
Home. sweet home.

348
00:38:49.480 --> 00:38:50.913
Yeah.

349
00:38:51.560 --> 00:38:53.869
I really thought
you were yanking my chain.

350
00:38:55.640 --> 00:38:57.756
What do you keep smiling at?

351
00:38:57.840 --> 00:39:00.115
You need a haircut.

352
00:39:00.840 --> 00:39:02.280
Oh. really?

353
00:39:02.280 --> 00:39:02.632
Oh. really?

354
00:39:10.360 --> 00:39:12.669
Maybe you ought to take me back inside.

355
00:39:26.080 --> 00:39:28.071
You see that?

356
00:39:32.120 --> 00:39:36.352
You mean the big-ass horse standing
in the middle of the jungle? Then. yeah.

357
00:39:58.680 --> 00:40:00.796
You know that horse. freckles?

358
00:40:04.480 --> 00:40:06.471
Yeah. I do.

359
00:40:18.280 --> 00:40:21.317
Tequila and tonic.
That's your drink. right?

360
00:40:23.000 --> 00:40:26.515
- Where's the tonic?
- We're running a little low on mixers.

361
00:40:32.840 --> 00:40:34.876
Sure you wanna waste that on me?

362
00:40:35.800 --> 00:40:37.836
I figured you could use a drink.

363
00:40:39.800 --> 00:40:41.791
I know I could.

364
00:40:43.440 --> 00:40:46.955
You gonna try to convince me that
everyone here doesn't hate me?

365
00:40:48.800 --> 00:40:53.032
Only if you're gonna try to convince me
every woman in the world's not crazy.

366
00:41:01.560 --> 00:41:06.554
When the alarm sounds. either you
or your partner must input the code.

367
00:41:07.480 --> 00:41:11.632
It is highly recommended that you and
your partner take alternating shifts.

368
00:41:11.720 --> 00:41:14.678
In this manner.
you will both stay as fresh and alert...

369
00:41:14.760 --> 00:41:17.228
...utmost importance
that when the alarm sounds.

370
00:41:17.320 --> 00:41:20.232
the code be entered correctly
and in a timely fashion.

371
00:41:20.320 --> 00:41:21.309
Here it comes.

372
00:41:21.400 --> 00:41:24.631
Do not attempt to use the computer
for anything else

373
00:41:24.720 --> 00:41:28.872
other than the entering of the code.
This is its only function.

374
00:41:28.960 --> 00:41:32.589
The isolation that attends the duties
associated with Station Three

375
00:41:32.680 --> 00:41:35.114
may tempt you
to try and utilise the computer

376
00:41:35.200 --> 00:41:39.079
for communication with the outside
world. This is strictly forbidden.

377
00:41:39.720 --> 00:41:42.029
Attempting to use
the computer in this manner

378
00:41:42.120 --> 00:41:45.430
will compromise
the integrity of the project and...

379
00:41:45.520 --> 00:41:48.114
worse. could lead to another incident.

380
00:41:49.200 --> 00:41:54.752
I repeat: do not use the computer for
anything other than entering the code.

381
00:41:56.560 --> 00:41:57.993
Congratulations.

382
00:41:58.080 --> 00:42:02.676
Until your replacements arrive. the
future of the project is in your hands.
